{"questionId":"22458118","questionHtml":"<p>The volume of a spherical bubble increases at a constant rate of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>.</p>\n<p>The initial volume of the bubble can be assumed to be zero.</p>\n<p>Find the rate, in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cm</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>, at which the radius of the bubble is increasing when the volume of the bubble is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempts to solve&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn></math>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>68389</mn><mo>…</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>15</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></msup></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;(seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempts to use the chain rule&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>r</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mr